## 12. CMS & Internal Linking (Implementation Layer)

At a high level, the CMS must support:

- **Clusters:** Services (Hire Talent categories), Industries.
- **Leaves:** Role pages, Resource items, Blog posts, Testimonials.
- **Relationships:**  
  - Roles ↔ Service cluster  
  - Roles ↔ Industries  
  - Roles ↔ Resources / Blog  
  - Industries ↔ Roles  
  - Industries ↔ Resources / Blog  
  - Testimonials ↔ Industries / Clusters

Internal linking rules:

- Every **role page** links to:
  - Its service cluster,
  - At least one industry,
  - At least one resource or blog post,
  - Contact/CTA.
- Every **industry page** links to:
  - 3–6 roles,
  - 1–3 relevant resources,
  - Contact/CTA.
- Resources and blog posts link **back** to relevant cluster/role/industry pages in body or CTA.

No page is a dead end; everything either loops into:

- A cluster,
- An industry,
- Or a conversion (Contact/Book a Consult).

